 \\nSystem: **Active sessions:**\\nSystem: - `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅ running (QLHV 5p — ~4h8m, child subagents completed normally)\\nSystem: - `cron:e7885813` ✅ running (Agent Status — new session, replaced old at 21:37)\\nSystem: - `cron:6f3323ef` ✅ running (DTLX 5p — status refresh, was completing when last logged)\\nSystem: - `telegram:group:-5163901258` ✅ running (stale ~39m, known)\\nSystem: - `main` ✅ done (expected)\\nSystem: \\nSystem: **Changes from last baseline (21:37):** None. All sessions stable. Child subagents of QLHV cron ended cleanly (normal completion), not as failures. No new failures, no blockers, no regressions.\\nSystem: \\nSystem: Pipeline stable. Silent.\\nSystem: [2026-04-14 21:47:03 UTC] Stable. No changes from last known state. All cron jobs running ok. Staying silent.\\nSystem: [2026-04-14 21:48:46 UTC] Comparing current sessions against heartbeat state (21:37 UTC):\\nSystem: \\nSystem: - `cron:ed2d0b5d` — still running ✅\\nSystem: - `cron:e7885813` — still running ✅  \\nSystem: - `cron:6f3323ef` — was \\\"done\\\" at 21:37, now running again (new cycle restart, expected behavior)\\nSystem: - `telegram:group:-5163901258` — still running, stale ~15h\\nSystem: - No failures, no blockers, pipeline healthy\\nSystem: \\nSystem: The `cron:6f3323ef` cycling back to \\\"running\\\" is normal cron restart behavior (5-minute cycle), not a state change. All systems nominal. Silent.\\n\\nRead HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\\nCurrent time: Tuesday, April 14th, 2026 - 9:50 PM (UTC) / 2026-04-14 21:50 UTC\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"timestamp\": 1776203458075,\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"11b3344b\",\n            \"s